26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_devinit_gm204.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "nv50.h"
30
31#include <subdev/bios.h>
32#include <subdev/bios/bit.h>
33#include <subdev/bios/pmu.h>
34
35static void
36pmu_code(struct nv50_devinit *init, u32 pmu, u32 img, u32 len, bool sec)
37{
38 struct nvkm_device *device = init->base.subdev.device;
39 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
40 int i;
41
42 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a180, 0x01000000 | (sec ? 0x10000000 : 0) | pmu);
43 for (i = 0; i < len; i += 4) {
44 if ((i & 0xff) == 0)
45 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a188, (pmu + i) >> 8);
46 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a184, nvbios_rd32(bios, img + i));
47 }
48
49 while (i & 0xff) {
50 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a184, 0x00000000);
51 i += 4;
52 }
53}
54
55static void
56pmu_data(struct nv50_devinit *init, u32 pmu, u32 img, u32 len)
57{
58 struct nvkm_device *device = init->base.subdev.device;
59 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
60 int i;
61
62 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a1c0, 0x01000000 | pmu);
63 for (i = 0; i < len; i += 4)
64 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a1c4, nvbios_rd32(bios, img + i));
65}
66
67static u32
68pmu_args(struct nv50_devinit *init, u32 argp, u32 argi)
69{
70 struct nvkm_device *device = init->base.subdev.device;
71 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a1c0, argp);
72 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a1c0, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10a1c4) + argi);
73 return nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10a1c4);
74}
75
76static void
77pmu_exec(struct nv50_devinit *init, u32 init_addr)
78{
79 struct nvkm_device *device = init->base.subdev.device;
80 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a104, init_addr);
81 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a10c, 0x00000000);
82 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a100, 0x00000002);
83}
84
85static int
86pmu_load(struct nv50_devinit *init, u8 type, bool post,
87 u32 *init_addr_pmu, u32 *args_addr_pmu)
88{
89 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &init->base.subdev;
90 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
91 struct nvbios_pmuR pmu;
92
93 if (!nvbios_pmuRm(bios, type, &pmu)) {
94 nvkm_error(subdev, "VBIOS PMU fuc %02x not found\n", type);
95 return -EINVAL;
96 }
97
98 if (!post)
99 return 0;
100
101 pmu_code(init, pmu.boot_addr_pmu, pmu.boot_addr, pmu.boot_size, false);
102 pmu_code(init, pmu.code_addr_pmu, pmu.code_addr, pmu.code_size, true);
103 pmu_data(init, pmu.data_addr_pmu, pmu.data_addr, pmu.data_size);
104
105 if (init_addr_pmu) {
106 *init_addr_pmu = pmu.init_addr_pmu;
107 *args_addr_pmu = pmu.args_addr_pmu;
108 return 0;
109 }
110
111 return pmu_exec(init, pmu.init_addr_pmu), 0;
112}
113
114static int
115gm204_devinit_post(struct nvkm_devinit *base, bool post)
116{
117 struct nv50_devinit *init = nv50_devinit(base);
118 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &init->base.subdev;
119 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
120 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
121 struct bit_entry bit_I;
122 u32 exec, args;
123 int ret;
124
125 if (bit_entry(bios, 'I', &bit_I) || bit_I.version != 1 ||
126 bit_I.length < 0x1c) {
127 nvkm_error(subdev, "VBIOS PMU init data not found\n");
128 return -EINVAL;
129 }
130
131 /* reset PMU and load init table parser ucode */
132 if (post) {
133 nvkm_mask(device, 0x000200, 0x00002000, 0x00000000);
134 nvkm_mask(device, 0x000200, 0x00002000, 0x00002000);
135 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000200);
136 while (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10a10c) & 0x00000006) {
137 }
138 }
139
140 ret = pmu_load(init, 0x04, post, &exec, &args);
141 if (ret)
142 return ret;
143
144 /* upload first chunk of init data */
145 if (post) {
146 u32 pmu = pmu_args(init, args + 0x08, 0x08);
147 u32 img = nvbios_rd16(bios, bit_I.offset + 0x14);
148 u32 len = nvbios_rd16(bios, bit_I.offset + 0x16);
149 pmu_data(init, pmu, img, len);
150 }
151
152 /* upload second chunk of init data */
153 if (post) {
154 u32 pmu = pmu_args(init, args + 0x08, 0x10);
155 u32 img = nvbios_rd16(bios, bit_I.offset + 0x18);
156 u32 len = nvbios_rd16(bios, bit_I.offset + 0x1a);
157 pmu_data(init, pmu, img, len);
158 }
159
160 /* execute init tables */
161 if (post) {
162 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10a040, 0x00005000);
163 pmu_exec(init, exec);
164 while (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10a040) & 0x00002000)) {
165 }
166 }
167
168 /* load and execute some other ucode image (bios therm?) */
169 return pmu_load(init, 0x01, post, NULL, NULL);
170}
171
172static const struct nvkm_devinit_func
173gm204_devinit = {
174 .preinit = nv50_devinit_preinit,
175 .init = nv50_devinit_init,
176 .post = gm204_devinit_post,
177 .pll_set = gf100_devinit_pll_set,
178 .disable = gm107_devinit_disable,
179};
180
181int
182gm204_devinit_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index,
183 struct nvkm_devinit **pinit)
184{
185 return nv50_devinit_new_(&gm204_devinit, device, index, pinit);
186}
